  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing Life-Saving Transportation Assistance to Refugees in Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since July 2017, Burundian refugees have been urged in various public fora by senior government officials in Tanzania to return home. To complement ongoing humanitarian efforts to provide for emergency and protection needs of refugees in Tanzania, IOM will: 1) provide refugees, with timely and safe transport, in a dignified manner, from entry points to camps, transfers from one camp to another, and/or for voluntary returns; and 2) ensure that each refugee in any mode of movement under IOM care, undergo a pre-embarkation medical screening, to ascertain fitness to travel, identify medical conditions that require further medical care, and/or for medical referrals.</narrative>
  </description>
